Subject: Re: [T2] Can I make my bus go lower by re-seting the spring 

Hi Volks,

Another temporary method to lower a bus is to simply fill it with cargo. 
Cement blocks, jugs of water, lumber, sand; whatever is handy.

One ton of cargo should drop the suspension about 2-3 inches.  Exceed 
that load at your own risk.

Happy Trails,

